Usage
-----

Use Ansible galaxy requirements.yml

    # {{role_name}} from eNiXHosting
    # private role
    - src: git+ssh://git@gitlab.enix.org/ansible/ansible-{{role_name}}.git
      name: eNiXHosting.{{role_name}}

    # public role
    - src: eNiXHosting.{{role_name}}

And add it to your play's roles:

    - hosts: all
      roles:
        - role eNiXHosting.{{role_name}}:
            {{role_name}}__var: true

You can also use the role as a playbook. You will be asked which hosts to provision, and you can further configure the play by using `--extra-vars`.

    $ ansible-playbook -i inventory --extra-vars='{...}' main.yml

